he interaction of people and the landscape, from the earliest Native American inhabitants and European explorers to the developers and residents of today's ever-expanding cities and suburbs. Many historical and contemporary maps and photographs illustrate the text.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCross Timbers (Okla. and Tex.). 0aHuman ecologyzCross Timbers (Okla. and Tex.). 0aHuman ecology-Cross Timbers (Okla. and Tex.). 0aNatural historyzCross Timbers (Okla. and Tex.). 0aNatural history-Cross Timbers (Okla. and Tex.). 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/72515740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292756380423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292756380/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK